-- Former Australian Prime Minister Rudd to Have Gallbladder Removed Today
-- Gemma Daley
-- 2010-07-30T05:57:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/former-australian-prime-minister-rudd-to-have-gallbladder-removed-today.html

          
          
             Former Australian Prime Minister
Kevin Rudd has been admitted to hospital to have his gallbladder
removed, a statement from his office said.  
 Rudd was taken to hospital with acute abdominal pain
yesterday and underwent a series of medical tests, the statement
said. The former prime minister is expected to remain in
hospital for the next few days, it said.  
